'''Sonjar''' was an [[artificer (Imaskari)|artificer]], and a senior [[wizard]] in service to the Lord Artificer during the last days of [[Imaskar]].{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|72}} [[Sonjar's Tower]] was his residence.

Per a sign on his abode, Sonjar called it the Amethyst Tower.{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|74}} His tower was built inside a geode; he was initially attracted to it by the concentration of earth power that it embodied.

Sonjar owned many slaves; after his death, four of them perished in the barracks{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|75}} and his favourite became a [[curst]].{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|76}} His chief cook ran away to join the Mulhorandi uprising.{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|77}} The artificer experimented on kidnapped priests; his last victim had been a [[Netherese]] priest of [[Moander]].{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|80}} His trophy room included the bone of a [[dinosaur]], the skull of a [[beholder]], a complete [[elf]] skeleton, and the preserved head of some angelic creature.{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|81}}

Sonjar had created a [[demiplane]], almost half a mile in diameter, to hold an orchard where he grew fruit trees such as [[apple]]s and [[pear]]s, and also kept [[bee|honey bees]].{{cite book/Lost Empires of Faerun|82}}
